<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<p id="Par40" class="p">The above calculation assumes 
 <inline-formula id="IEq33" class="inline-formula">
  <alternatives class="alternatives">
   <tex-math id="M95" class="tex-math">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \usepackage{upgreek} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document}$$C &lt; \frac{W}{{\lambda _{\mathrm{R}}}}$$\end{document}</tex-math>
   <math id="M96" class="math">
    <mi class="mi">C</mi>
    <mo class="mo">&lt;</mo>
    <mfrac class="mfrac">
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi class="mi">W</mi>
     </mrow>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <msub class="msub">
       <mrow class="mrow">
        <mi class="mi">λ</mi>
       </mrow>
       <mrow class="mrow">
        <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">R</mi>
       </mrow>
      </msub>
     </mrow>
    </mfrac>
   </math>
   <inline-graphic xlink:href="41467_2018_4968_Article_IEq33.gif" class="inline-graphic" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
  </alternatives>
 </inline-formula> but we have 
 <inline-formula id="IEq34" class="inline-formula">
  <alternatives class="alternatives">
   <tex-math id="M97" class="tex-math">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \usepackage{upgreek} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document}$$C^ \ast = c_{\mathrm{R}}^ \ast + c_{\mathrm{P}}^ \ast = \frac{W}{3}$$\end{document}</tex-math>
   <math id="M98" class="math">
    <msup class="msup">
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi class="mi">C</mi>
     </mrow>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mo class="mo">*</mo>
     </mrow>
    </msup>
    <mo class="mo">=</mo>
    <msubsup class="msubsup">
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi class="mi">c</mi>
     </mrow>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">R</mi>
     </mrow>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mo class="mo">*</mo>
     </mrow>
    </msubsup>
    <mo class="mo">+</mo>
    <msubsup class="msubsup">
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi class="mi">c</mi>
     </mrow>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">P</mi>
     </mrow>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mo class="mo">*</mo>
     </mrow>
    </msubsup>
    <mo class="mo">=</mo>
    <mfrac class="mfrac">
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi class="mi">W</mi>
     </mrow>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mn class="mn">3</mn>
     </mrow>
    </mfrac>
   </math>
   <inline-graphic xlink:href="41467_2018_4968_Article_IEq34.gif" class="inline-graphic" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
  </alternatives>
 </inline-formula> and so the above calculation is only valid for 
 <italic class="italic">λ</italic>
 <sub class="sub">R</sub> ≤ 3. For 
 <italic class="italic">λ</italic>
 <sub class="sub">R</sub> &gt; 3 the risk for the rich vanishes 
 <italic class="italic">p</italic>
 <sub class="sub">R</sub> = 0 and so the payoff is maximized by using the minimal value of 
 <italic class="italic">c</italic>
 <sub class="sub">R</sub> that keeps the risk at a value of 0 (Eq. (
 <xref rid="Equ5" ref-type="" class="xref">5)</xref>). Thus the best response for the rich is now 
 <inline-formula id="IEq35" class="inline-formula">
  <alternatives class="alternatives">
   <tex-math id="M99" class="tex-math">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \usepackage{upgreek} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document}$$c_{\mathrm{R}} = \frac{W}{{\lambda _{\mathrm{R}}}} - c_{\mathrm{P}}$$\end{document}</tex-math>
   <math id="M100" class="math">
    <msub class="msub">
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi class="mi">c</mi>
     </mrow>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">R</mi>
     </mrow>
    </msub>
    <mo class="mo">=</mo>
    <mfrac class="mfrac">
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi class="mi">W</mi>
     </mrow>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <msub class="msub">
       <mrow class="mrow">
        <mi class="mi">λ</mi>
       </mrow>
       <mrow class="mrow">
        <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">R</mi>
       </mrow>
      </msub>
     </mrow>
    </mfrac>
    <mo class="mo">-</mo>
    <msub class="msub">
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi class="mi">c</mi>
     </mrow>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">P</mi>
     </mrow>
    </msub>
   </math>
   <inline-graphic xlink:href="41467_2018_4968_Article_IEq35.gif" class="inline-graphic" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
  </alternatives>
 </inline-formula> but the response for the poor stays the same (Eq. (
 <xref rid="Equ12" ref-type="" class="xref">12)</xref>). The intersection is
 <disp-formula id="Equ15" class="disp-formula">
  <label class="label">15</label>
  <alternatives class="alternatives">
   <tex-math id="M101" class="tex-math">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \usepackage{upgreek} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document}$$c_{\mathrm{R}}^ \ast = 2\frac{{W_{\mathrm{R}} + W_{\mathrm{P}}}}{{\lambda _{\mathrm{R}}}} - W_{\mathrm{P}}$$\end{document}</tex-math>
   <math id="M102" display="block" class="math">
    <msubsup class="msubsup">
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi class="mi">c</mi>
     </mrow>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">R</mi>
     </mrow>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mo class="mo">*</mo>
     </mrow>
    </msubsup>
    <mo class="mo">=</mo>
    <mn class="mn">2</mn>
    <mfrac class="mfrac">
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <msub class="msub">
       <mrow class="mrow">
        <mi class="mi">W</mi>
       </mrow>
       <mrow class="mrow">
        <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">R</mi>
       </mrow>
      </msub>
      <mo class="mo">+</mo>
      <msub class="msub">
       <mrow class="mrow">
        <mi class="mi">W</mi>
       </mrow>
       <mrow class="mrow">
        <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">P</mi>
       </mrow>
      </msub>
     </mrow>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <msub class="msub">
       <mrow class="mrow">
        <mi class="mi">λ</mi>
       </mrow>
       <mrow class="mrow">
        <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">R</mi>
       </mrow>
      </msub>
     </mrow>
    </mfrac>
    <mo class="mo">-</mo>
    <msub class="msub">
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi class="mi">W</mi>
     </mrow>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">P</mi>
     </mrow>
    </msub>
   </math>
   <graphic xlink:href="41467_2018_4968_Article_Equ15.gif" position="anchor" class="graphic" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
  </alternatives>
 </disp-formula>
 <disp-formula id="Equ16" class="disp-formula">
  <label class="label">16</label>
  <alternatives class="alternatives">
   <tex-math id="M103" class="tex-math">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \usepackage{upgreek} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document}$$c_{\mathrm{P}}^ \ast = W_{\mathrm{P}} - \frac{{W_{\mathrm{R}} + W_{\mathrm{P}}}}{{\lambda _{\mathrm{R}}}},$$\end{document}</tex-math>
   <math id="M104" display="block" class="math">
    <msubsup class="msubsup">
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi class="mi">c</mi>
     </mrow>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">P</mi>
     </mrow>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mo class="mo">*</mo>
     </mrow>
    </msubsup>
    <mo class="mo">=</mo>
    <msub class="msub">
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi class="mi">W</mi>
     </mrow>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">P</mi>
     </mrow>
    </msub>
    <mo class="mo">-</mo>
    <mfrac class="mfrac">
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <msub class="msub">
       <mrow class="mrow">
        <mi class="mi">W</mi>
       </mrow>
       <mrow class="mrow">
        <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">R</mi>
       </mrow>
      </msub>
      <mo class="mo">+</mo>
      <msub class="msub">
       <mrow class="mrow">
        <mi class="mi">W</mi>
       </mrow>
       <mrow class="mrow">
        <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">P</mi>
       </mrow>
      </msub>
     </mrow>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <msub class="msub">
       <mrow class="mrow">
        <mi class="mi">λ</mi>
       </mrow>
       <mrow class="mrow">
        <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">R</mi>
       </mrow>
      </msub>
     </mrow>
    </mfrac>
    <mo class="mo">,</mo>
   </math>
   <graphic xlink:href="41467_2018_4968_Article_Equ16.gif" position="anchor" class="graphic" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
  </alternatives>
 </disp-formula>which is non-negative for 
 <inline-formula id="IEq36" class="inline-formula">
  <alternatives class="alternatives">
   <tex-math id="M105" class="tex-math">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \usepackage{upgreek} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document}$$\lambda _{\mathrm{R}} &lt; 2\frac{{W_{\mathrm{R}} + W_{\mathrm{P}}}}{{W_{\mathrm{P}}}}$$\end{document}</tex-math>
   <math id="M106" class="math">
    <msub class="msub">
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi class="mi">λ</mi>
     </mrow>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">R</mi>
     </mrow>
    </msub>
    <mo class="mo">&lt;</mo>
    <mn class="mn">2</mn>
    <mfrac class="mfrac">
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <msub class="msub">
       <mrow class="mrow">
        <mi class="mi">W</mi>
       </mrow>
       <mrow class="mrow">
        <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">R</mi>
       </mrow>
      </msub>
      <mo class="mo">+</mo>
      <msub class="msub">
       <mrow class="mrow">
        <mi class="mi">W</mi>
       </mrow>
       <mrow class="mrow">
        <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">P</mi>
       </mrow>
      </msub>
     </mrow>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <msub class="msub">
       <mrow class="mrow">
        <mi class="mi">W</mi>
       </mrow>
       <mrow class="mrow">
        <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">P</mi>
       </mrow>
      </msub>
     </mrow>
    </mfrac>
   </math>
   <inline-graphic xlink:href="41467_2018_4968_Article_IEq36.gif" class="inline-graphic" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
  </alternatives>
 </inline-formula> (with 
 <inline-formula id="IEq37" class="inline-formula">
  <alternatives class="alternatives">
   <tex-math id="M107" class="tex-math">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \usepackage{upgreek} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document}$$2\frac{{W_{\mathrm{R}} + W_{\mathrm{P}}}}{{W_{\mathrm{P}}}}\, \in \,\left[ {4,6} \right]$$\end{document}</tex-math>
   <math id="M108" class="math">
    <mn class="mn">2</mn>
    <mfrac class="mfrac">
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <msub class="msub">
       <mrow class="mrow">
        <mi class="mi">W</mi>
       </mrow>
       <mrow class="mrow">
        <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">R</mi>
       </mrow>
      </msub>
      <mo class="mo">+</mo>
      <msub class="msub">
       <mrow class="mrow">
        <mi class="mi">W</mi>
       </mrow>
       <mrow class="mrow">
        <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">P</mi>
       </mrow>
      </msub>
     </mrow>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <msub class="msub">
       <mrow class="mrow">
        <mi class="mi">W</mi>
       </mrow>
       <mrow class="mrow">
        <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">P</mi>
       </mrow>
      </msub>
     </mrow>
    </mfrac>
    <mspace width="0.3em" class="mspace"/>
    <mo class="mo">∈</mo>
    <mspace width="0.3em" class="mspace"/>
    <mfenced close="]" open="[" separators="" class="mfenced">
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mn class="mn">4</mn>
      <mo class="mo">,</mo>
      <mn class="mn">6</mn>
     </mrow>
    </mfenced>
   </math>
   <inline-graphic xlink:href="41467_2018_4968_Article_IEq37.gif" class="inline-graphic" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
  </alternatives>
 </inline-formula> considering the condition for case 1. For even higher 
 <italic class="italic">λ</italic>
 <sub class="sub">R</sub> the lines do not cross anymore. The minimum requirement for 
 <italic class="italic">p</italic>
 <sub class="sub">R</sub> = 0 is 
 <inline-formula id="IEq38" class="inline-formula">
  <alternatives class="alternatives">
   <tex-math id="M109" class="tex-math">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \usepackage{upgreek} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document}$$c_{\mathrm{R}} + c_{\mathrm{P}} \ge \frac{{W_{\mathrm{P}}}}{2}$$\end{document}</tex-math>
   <math id="M110" class="math">
    <msub class="msub">
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi class="mi">c</mi>
     </mrow>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">R</mi>
     </mrow>
    </msub>
    <mo class="mo">+</mo>
    <msub class="msub">
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi class="mi">c</mi>
     </mrow>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">P</mi>
     </mrow>
    </msub>
    <mo class="mo">≥</mo>
    <mfrac class="mfrac">
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <msub class="msub">
       <mrow class="mrow">
        <mi class="mi">W</mi>
       </mrow>
       <mrow class="mrow">
        <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">P</mi>
       </mrow>
      </msub>
     </mrow>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mn class="mn">2</mn>
     </mrow>
    </mfrac>
   </math>
   <inline-graphic xlink:href="41467_2018_4968_Article_IEq38.gif" class="inline-graphic" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
  </alternatives>
 </inline-formula> which corresponds exactly to the amount that the poor player contributes (Eq. (
 <xref rid="Equ12" ref-type="" class="xref">12)</xref>) if the rich contributes nothing, so 
 <inline-formula id="IEq39" class="inline-formula">
  <alternatives class="alternatives">
   <tex-math id="M111" class="tex-math">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \usepackage{upgreek} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document}$$c_{\mathrm{R}}^ \ast = 0$$\end{document}</tex-math>
   <math id="M112" class="math">
    <msubsup class="msubsup">
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi class="mi">c</mi>
     </mrow>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">R</mi>
     </mrow>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mo class="mo">*</mo>
     </mrow>
    </msubsup>
    <mo class="mo">=</mo>
    <mn class="mn">0</mn>
   </math>
   <inline-graphic xlink:href="41467_2018_4968_Article_IEq39.gif" class="inline-graphic" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
  </alternatives>
 </inline-formula> and 
 <inline-formula id="IEq40" class="inline-formula">
  <alternatives class="alternatives">
   <tex-math id="M113" class="tex-math">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \usepackage{upgreek} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document}$$c_{\mathrm{P}}^ \ast = \frac{{W_{\mathrm{P}}}}{2}$$\end{document}</tex-math>
   <math id="M114" class="math">
    <msubsup class="msubsup">
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi class="mi">c</mi>
     </mrow>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">P</mi>
     </mrow>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mo class="mo">*</mo>
     </mrow>
    </msubsup>
    <mo class="mo">=</mo>
    <mfrac class="mfrac">
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <msub class="msub">
       <mrow class="mrow">
        <mi class="mi">W</mi>
       </mrow>
       <mrow class="mrow">
        <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">P</mi>
       </mrow>
      </msub>
     </mrow>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mn class="mn">2</mn>
     </mrow>
    </mfrac>
   </math>
   <inline-graphic xlink:href="41467_2018_4968_Article_IEq40.gif" class="inline-graphic" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
  </alternatives>
 </inline-formula>.
</p>
